---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of Service | Vertical Image Research"
  description="Terms of Service for Vertical Image Research."
  showGate={false}
>
  <section class="legal-page">
    <div class="shell legal-shell">
      <p class="eyebrow">LEGAL</p>
      <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
      <p class="effective"><strong>Effective date:</strong> July 13, 2026</p>

      <p>These Terms of Service ("Terms") govern your use of <strong>Vertical Image Research</strong> (the "App"), a private web-based research dashboard operated by <strong>Edith Jenius</strong> ("we", "us", or "our").</p>
      <p>By using the App, you agree to these Terms.</p>

      <h2>1. The App</h2>
      <p>Vertical Image Research helps an authorized TikTok user view that user's own public TikTok profile information and recent public videos in an organized dashboard for personal research and review.</p>
      <p>The App does not provide content-posting, advertising-management, account-management, or bulk video-download features.</p>

      <h2>2. Eligibility and account authorization</h2>
      <p>You may use the App only if you can lawfully agree to these Terms and comply with TikTok's applicable terms and policies. When you choose to connect TikTok, you authorize the App through TikTok's authorization flow. You are responsible for keeping your TikTok account credentials private; the App does not ask for or store your TikTok password.</p>

      <h2>3. Acceptable use</h2>
      <p>You agree not to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>use the App to violate law or the rights of others;</li>
        <li>attempt to access data that you have not been authorized to access;</li>
        <li>interfere with, disrupt, or abuse the App, TikTok, or related services;</li>
        <li>use the App to circumvent platform restrictions or collect content in a manner prohibited by TikTok's policies.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>4. Third-party services</h2>
      <p>The App uses TikTok services when you choose to connect your account. Your use of TikTok remains subject to TikTok's own terms, privacy policies, and platform rules. We are not responsible for third-party services or their availability.</p>

      <h2>5. Intellectual property</h2>
      <p>The App and its original interface, code, and documentation are owned by us or our licensors. Content displayed from TikTok remains subject to the rights and platform terms applicable to that content. These Terms do not grant you ownership of third-party content.</p>

      <h2>6. Availability and changes</h2>
      <p>The App is provided on an "as is" and "as available" basis. We may modify, suspend, or discontinue any part of the App when reasonably necessary, including to comply with platform requirements or law.</p>

      <h2>7. Disclaimer and limitation of liability</h2>
      <p>To the maximum extent permitted by law, we make no warranties about the App's availability, accuracy, or fitness for a particular purpose. We are not liable for indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or punitive damages arising from your use of the App.</p>

      <h2>8. Termination</h2>
      <p>You may stop using the App at any time and may revoke the App's access through TikTok's account settings where available. We may suspend or terminate access when we reasonably believe these Terms, platform rules, or law have been violated.</p>

      <h2>9. Changes to these Terms</h2>
      <p>We may update these Terms from time to time. We will post the updated version on this page and revise the effective date. Continued use after an update means you accept the revised Terms.</p>

      <h2>10. Contact</h2>
      <p>For questions about these Terms, contact: <strong>jeniusedith@gmail.com</strong>.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .legal-page { padding: 74px 0 20px; }
  .legal-shell { max-width: 820px; }
  h1 { margin: 0 0 18px; font-family: Georgia, "Noto Serif SC", serif; font-size: clamp(44px, 6vw, 68px); font-weight: 500; line-height: 1.08; }
  .effective { margin: 0 0 34px; color: var(--muted); }
  p, li { color: var(--muted); font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.85; }
  p { margin: 0 0 18px; }
  h2 { margin: 42px 0 12px; font-family: Georgia, "Noto Serif SC", serif; font-size: 26px; font-weight: 500; }
  ul { margin: 0 0 20px 20px; padding: 0; }
  strong { color: var(--ink); }
</style>
